introduction.Protein: Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 4

summary_and_characteristics.Function Descriptions: Receptor for TNFSF4/OX40L/GP34. Is a costimulatory molecule implicated in long-term T-cell immunity. . (Microbial infection) Acts as a receptor for human herpesvirus 6B/HHV-6B. .

UniProt Synonyms: Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 4
